author: Sergio Bustos and Jill Colvin, Associated Press
title: Donald Trump pans Iowa polls, says Carson 'super low-energy'
text: Photo: Alan Diaz, AP Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump gestures as he addresses supporters during a campaign stop at the Trump National Doral Miami resort, Friday, Oct. 23, 2015 in Doral, Fla.. Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump gestures as he... MIAMI (AP) — Republican presidential front-runner Donald Trump dismissed polls that show him trailing Dr. Ben Carson in Iowa, calling the retired neurosurgeon "super low-energy" before a boisterous crowd in Miami on Friday night.
